'''Carlo Lombardi''' (1900â€“1984) was an Italian [[actor|stage]] and [[film actor]]. Later in his career he often worked in [[television]]. He appeared in a number of films during the [[Fascist era]], including a leading role in the historical epic ''[[Scipio Africanus: The Defeat of Hannibal|Scipio Africanus]]'' (1937).<ref>Elley p.196</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[The Man with the Claw]]'' (1931)
* ''[[Pergolesi (film)|Pergolesi]]'' (1932)
* ''[[Zaganella and the Cavalier]]'' (1932)
* ''[[The Gift of the Morning]]'' (1932)
* ''[[Everybody's Woman]]'' (1934)
* ''[[The Anonymous Roylott]]'' (1936)
* ''[[Scipio Africanus: The Defeat of Hannibal|Scipio Africanus]]'' (1937)
* ''[[The Last Enemy (film)|The Last Enemy]]'' (1938)
* ''[[Star of the Sea (1938 film)|Star of the Sea]]'' (1938)
* ''[[A Wife in Danger]]'' (1939)
* ''[[The Castle Ball]]'' (1939)
* ''[[A Thousand Lire a Month]]'' (1939)
* ''[[The First Woman Who Passes]]'' (1940)
* ''[[Luce nelle tenebre]]'' (1941)
* ''[[L'attore scomparso]]'' (1941)
* ''[[The Secret Lover]]'' (1941)
* ''[[Headlights in the Fog]]'' (1942)
* ''[[The Tyrant of Padua]]'' (1946)
* ''[[The Devil's Gondola]]'' (1946)
* ''[[Baron Carlo Mazza]]'' (1948)
* ''[[Il nido di Falasco]]'' (1950)
* ''[[Orphan of the Ghetto]]'' (1954)
* ''[[The Giant of Marathon]]'' (1959)
* ''[[Hawk of the Caribbean]]'' (1962)

